  "text": "In systems driven by customer orders, manufacturers hold little finished inventory because they customize all products to meet individual orders. On the downside, order-driven production responds to swings in demand and thus varies in capacity utilization and may suffer from long order lead times because the system holds no products in stock [CITATION_1] .",
